Limpieza de datos

## funcion cargar data
cargaLimpieza <- function(ruta){
  library(readr)
  datos <- read_delim(ruta, 
    delim = ",", escape_double = FALSE, locale = locale(encoding = "WINDOWS-1252"), 
    trim_ws = TRUE)
}

## funcion renombrar columnas
renColumnas <-function(df, vectorNom){
  if (!is.character(vectorNom)) {
    stop("Debe ser un valor de tipo texto o character")
  }
  colnames(df) <- vectorNom 
  datos <- as.data.frame(df)
  return(datos)
}

## funci√≥n Limpiar datos con Mediana, Media y Moda
limpCol <- function(dfCol){
  
  #Datos de Texto
  if (!is.numeric(dfCol)) {
    
    library(modeest)

    modaCol <- mfv(dfCol)
    
    dfCol <- ifelse(is.na(dfCol), modaCol, dfCol)
        
    return(dfCol)
        
    stop()
  
  #Datos N√∫mericos    
  }else{
  
    #Test de normalidad para conocer el valor de p
    resultado<-shapiro.test(dfCol)
    
    if (resultado$p.value < 0.05){
      print("Mediana")
      
      print(median(dfCol, na.rm = TRUE))
      
      dfCol <- ifelse(is.na(dfCol), median(dfCol, na.rm = TRUE), dfCol)
      
    }else{
      print("Media")
      
      print(mean(dfCol, na.rm = TRUE))
      
      dfCol <- ifelse(is.na(dfCol), mean(dfCol, na.rm = TRUE), dfCol)
    }
  }
}

## funcion correlacion
corVar <- function(df){
  library(corrplot)
  cor <-corrplot.mixed(cor(df), lower="ellipse", upper="number", order="hclust")
  return(cor)
}

##funcion normalizaci√≥n
norm_minmax <- function(x){
  (x- min(x)) /(max(x)-min(x))
}

## DIAGRAMAS PERSONALIZADOS

create_beautiful_radarchart <- function(data, color = "#00AFBB", 
                                        vlabels = colnames(data), vlcex = 0.7,
                                        caxislabels = NULL, title = 'Grasas de Sandwich por Restaurantes'){
  radarchart(
    data, axistype = 1,
    # Customize the polygon
    pcol = color, pfcol = scales::alpha(color, 0.5), plwd = 2, plty = 1,
    # Customize the grid
    cglcol = "grey", cglty = 1, cglwd = 0.8,
    # Customize the axis
    axislabcol = "grey", 
    # Variable labels
    vlcex = vlcex, vlabels = vlabels,
    caxislabels = caxislabels, title = title
  )
}

## DIAGRAMA DE RADAR PARA TODOS LOS RESTAURANTES

op <- par(mar = c(1, 1, 1, 1))

  color = c("#fffd00", "#0205ff", "#ff2b01", "#00ff01", "#b5cd54", "#699788", "#650b6c")
)

legend(
  x = "bottom", legend = rownames(dataFinal[-c(1,2),]), horiz = TRUE,

  text.col = "black", cex = 0.7, pt.cex = 0.7
  )

par(op)

## DIAGRAMA DE RADAR POR RESTAURANTE

# Define colors and titles
colors <- c("#fffd00", "#0205ff", "#ff2b01", "#00ff01", "#b5cd54", "#699788", "#650b6c")
titles <- c("Arbys", "Burger King", "Chick Fil-A", "Dairy Queen", "Mcdonalds", "Sonic", "Subway")

# Reduce plot margin using par()
# Split the screen in 3 parts
op <- par(mar = c(1, 1, 1, 1))
par(mfrow = c(1,7))

# Create the radar chart
for(i in 1:7){
  create_beautiful_radarchart(
    data = dataFinal[c(1, 2, i+2), ], caxislabels = c(0, 0.2, 0.4, 0.6, 1),
    color = colors[i], title = titles[i]
    )
}

par(op)
